def filter_dog_cat(model, im_file, topn=5):
    outliers = []
    for main_dir, sub_dir, file_name_list in os.walk(im_file):
        total = len(file_name_list)
        count = 0
        if not os.path.exists(outliers_path):
            os.mkdir(outliers_path)
        for filename in file_name_list:
            count += 1
            file_path = os.path.join(main_dir, filename)
            img = image.load_img(file_path, target_size=(224, 224))
            x = image.img_to_array(img)
            x = np.expand_dims(x, axis=0)
            x = preprocess_input(x)
            preds = model.predict(x)
            topn_preds = decode_predictions(preds, top=topn)[0]
            topn_code = [x[0] for x in topn_preds]
            is_dog = len(set(topn_code) & set(dogs)) > 0
            is_cat = len(set(topn_code) & set(cats)) > 0
            is_outlier = not is_dog and not is_cat
            print("progress:{}/{},image:{},is_outlier:{},info:{}".format(count, total, filename, is_outlier,
                                                                            topn_code),end='\r')
            if is_outlier:
                outliers.append(filename)
                shutil.move(file_path,outliers_path) # outliers
        break  # 
    return outliers

# 
model = ResNet50(weights='imagenet')
outlier_img = filter_dog_cat(model, img_path, 50)
print(outlier_img)

def get_outlier_img_path(outliers_path):
    outlier_img = []
    for main_dir, sub_dir, file_name_list in os.walk(outliers_path):
        for filename in file_name_list:
            file_path = os.path.join(main_dir, filename)
            outlier_img.append(file_path)
    return outlier_img
outlier_img_path = get_outlier_img_path(outliers_path)

# Define your transforms for the training, validation, and testing sets
mean = [0.485, 0.456, 0.406]
std = [0.229, 0.224, 0.225]
main_dir = 'images'
train_dir = os.path.join(main_dir,'train')
valid_dir = os.path.join(main_dir,'valid')
test_dir = os.path.join(main_dir,'test')

train_transforms = transforms.Compose([transforms.Resize(256),
                                       transforms.CenterCrop(224),
                                       transforms.RandomRotation(30),
                                       transforms.RandomResizedCrop(224),
                                       transforms.RandomHorizontalFlip(),
                                       transforms.ToTensor(),
                                       transforms.Normalize(mean=mean,std=std)])
valid_transforms = transforms.Compose([transforms.Resize(256),
                                       transforms.CenterCrop(224),
                                       transforms.ToTensor(),
                                       transforms.Normalize(mean=mean,std=std)])


# Load the datasets with ImageFolder
train_data = datasets.ImageFolder(train_dir, transform=train_transforms)
valid_data = datasets.ImageFolder(valid_dir, transform=valid_transforms)

# Using the image datasets and the trainforms, define the dataloaders
batch_size = 32
train_loader = torch.utils.data.DataLoader(train_data, batch_size=batch_size, shuffle=True)
valid_loader = torch.utils.data.DataLoader(valid_data, batch_size=batch_size)

# vgg16
def get_vgg16_model():
    model = models.vgg16(pretrained=True)

    for param in model.parameters():
        param.requires_grad = False
    
    # ,
    model.classifier[6] = torch.nn.Linear(4096, 2)
    
    return model

#vgg19
def get_vgg19_model():
    model = models.vgg19(pretrained=True)
    
    for param in model.parameters():
        param.requires_grad = False
    
    # ,
    model.classifier[6] = torch.nn.Linear(4096, 2)
    
    return model
# resnet50
def get_resnet50_model():
    model = models.resnet50(pretrained=True)
    
    for param in model.parameters():
        param.requires_grad = False
    
    # ,
    model.fc = torch.nn.Linear(2048, 2)
    
    return model

# alexnet
def get_alexnet_model():
    model = models.alexnet(pretrained=True)
    
    for param in model.parameters():
        param.requires_grad = False
    
    # ,
    model.classifier[6] = torch.nn.Linear(4096, 2)
    
    return model

训练和验证¶

In [9]:
def do_deep_learning(model, trainloader, validloader, epochs, criterion, optimizer, scheduler, device='cuda'):   
    print("="*30,"train start","="*30)
    start_time = time.time()
    epochs = epochs
    model.to(device)

    train_loss_list = []
    train_acc_list = []
    valid_loss_list = []   
    valid_acc_list = []
    result_list = []
    
    for epoch in range(epochs):
        # train
        scheduler.step() 
        model.train()
        train_loss = 0
        train_corrects = 0
        train_total = 0
        for index, (inputs, labels) in enumerate(trainloader):
            inputs, labels = inputs.to(device), labels.to(device)
            optimizer.zero_grad()
            # Forward and backward passes
            # outputs = model.forward(inputs)
            outputs = model(inputs)
            _, preds = torch.max(outputs,1)          
            loss = criterion(outputs, labels)
            loss.backward()
            optimizer.step()
            train_loss += loss.item() * inputs.size(0)
            train_corrects += (preds == labels.data).sum().item()
            train_total += inputs.size(0)
            
         
        # valid
        model.eval()
        valid_loss = 0
        valid_corrects = 0
        valid_total = 0
        with torch.no_grad():           
            for index,(inputs, labels) in enumerate(validloader):
                inputs, labels = inputs.to(device), labels.to(device)
                outputs = model(inputs)
                _, preds = torch.max(outputs,1)
                loss = criterion(outputs, labels)
                valid_loss += loss.item() * inputs.size(0)
                valid_corrects += (preds == labels.data).sum().item()
                valid_total += inputs.size(0)


                
        train_loss = train_loss/train_total
        train_acc = train_corrects/train_total
        valid_loss = valid_loss/valid_total
        valid_acc = valid_corrects/valid_total
        
        train_loss_list.append(train_loss)
        train_acc_list.append(train_acc)
        valid_loss_list.append(valid_loss)
        valid_acc_list.append(valid_acc)
        
        result_d = {
            'epoch':epoch+1,
            'train_total':train_total,
            'train_loss':train_loss,
            'valid_total':valid_total,
            'valid_loss':valid_loss
        }
        result_list.append(result_d)
        
        print("Epoch: {}/{} ".format(epoch+1, epochs),
              "Train Total: {}".format(train_total),
              "Train Loss: {:.4f}".format(train_loss),
              "Train Acc: {:.4f}".format(train_acc),
              "Valid Total: {}".format(valid_total),
              "Valid Loss: {:.4f}".format(valid_loss),
              "Valid Acc: {:.4f}".format(valid_acc))
   

    plt.figure(1,figsize=(16,5))
    plt.subplot(1,2,1)
    plt.plot(train_loss_list, 'r-', mec='k', label='train_loss', lw=2)
    plt.plot(valid_loss_list, 'g-', mec='k', label='valid_loss', lw=2)
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('train loss')
    plt.xlabel('steps')
    plt.ylabel('loss')
    
    plt.subplot(1,2,2)
    plt.plot(train_acc_list, 'r-', mec='k', label='train_acc', lw=2)
    plt.plot(valid_acc_list, 'g-', mec='k', label='valid_acc', lw=2)
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('train acc')
    plt.xlabel('steps')
    plt.ylabel('acc')
    plt.show()
    
    end_time = time.time() - start_time
    print("train time is :{:.0f}m {:.4f}s".format(end_time//60,end_time%60))
    print("="*30,"train end","="*30)
    return result_list
    
def check_accuracy_on_test(testloader, criterion ,device='cuda'): 
    print("="*30,"valid start","="*30)
    start_time = time.time()
    correct = 0
    total = 0
    val_loss = 0
    with torch.no_grad():
        for data in testloader:
            images, labels = data
            images = images.to(device)
            labels = labels.to(device)
            outputs = model(images)
            _, predicted = torch.max(outputs.data, 1)
            total += labels.size(0)
            correct += (predicted == labels).sum().item()
            val_loss += criterion(outputs, labels).item()

    print('val_total : {},val_loss : {},val_acc:{}'.format(total, val_loss / total,correct / total))
    end_time = time.time() - start_time
    print("valid time is :{:.0f}m {:.4f}s".format(end_time//60,end_time%60))
    print("="*30,"valid end","="*30)

def my_func(d, model_name, optimizer_name):
    d['model'] = model_name
    d['optimizer'] = optimizer_name
    return d

LR = 0.001 
epochs = 20
device = torch.device('cuda' if torch.cuda.is_available() else 'cpu')    
loss_func = torch.nn.CrossEntropyLoss() #

for i in range(4):
    torch.cuda.empty_cache()
    model = get_vgg16_model()
    opt_SGD         = torch.optim.SGD(model.classifier.parameters(), weight_decay=0.1, lr=LR)
    opt_Momentum    = torch.optim.SGD(model.classifier.parameters(), weight_decay=0.1, lr=LR, momentum=0.8)
    opt_RMSprop     = torch.optim.RMSprop(model.classifier.parameters(), weight_decay=0.1, lr=LR, alpha=0.9)
    opt_Adam        = torch.optim.Adam(model.classifier.parameters(), weight_decay=0.1, lr=LR, betas=(0.9, 0.99))
    optimizer = None  
    optimizer_name = None
    if i == 1 :
        optimizer = opt_SGD
        optimizer_name = 'opt_SGD'
    elif i == 2 :
        optimizer = opt_Momentum
        optimizer_name = 'opt_Momentum'
    elif i == 3 :
        optimizer = opt_RMSprop
        optimizer_name = 'opt_RMSprop'
    else :
        optimizer = opt_Adam
        optimizer_name = 'opt_Adam'
       
    print(optimizer)
    scheduler = torch.optim.lr_scheduler.StepLR(optimizer, step_size=3, gamma=0.1)
    result_l = do_deep_learning(model, train_loader, valid_loader, epochs, loss_func, optimizer, scheduler,device)
    result_total += [my_func(d,'vgg16',optimizer_name) for d in result_l]

    opt_RMSprop     = torch.optim.RMSprop(model.classifier.parameters(), weight_decay=0.1, lr=LR, alpha=0.9)
    opt_Adam        = torch.optim.Adam(model.classifier.parameters(), weight_decay=0.1, lr=LR, betas=(0.9, 0.99))
    optimizer = None       
    optimizer_name = None
    if i == 1 :
        optimizer = opt_SGD
        optimizer_name = 'opt_SGD'
    elif i == 2 :
        optimizer = opt_Momentum
        optimizer_name = 'opt_Momentum'
    elif i == 3 :
        optimizer = opt_RMSprop
        optimizer_name = 'opt_RMSprop'
    else :
        optimizer = opt_Adam
        optimizer_name = 'opt_Adam'
        
    print(optimizer) 
    scheduler = torch.optim.lr_scheduler.StepLR(optimizer, step_size=3, gamma=0.1)

def process_image(image):
    ''' Scales, crops, and normalizes a PIL image for a PyTorch model,
        returns an Numpy array
    '''
    # TODO: Process a PIL image for use in a PyTorch model
    pil_image = image
    # pil_image = pil_image.resize((256,256))
    # pil_image = pil_image.crop((0,0,224,224))
    pil_image = pil_image.resize((224,224))
    
    np_image = np.array(pil_image)  / 255
    np_image = (np_image - mean) / std 
    # 
    np_image = np_image.transpose(2,0,1)
    return np_image

def predict(image_path, model,device='cuda',topk=2):

    model= model.to(device)
    model.eval()
    # TODO: Implement the code to predict the class from an image file
    pil_img= Image.open(image_path)
    #print(pil_img)
    processed_image= process_image(pil_img)
    torch_image= torch.from_numpy(processed_image)
    torch_image= torch_image.unsqueeze_(0)
    torch_image= torch_image.float().to(device)
    output= model.forward(torch_image)
    ps = torch.exp(output)
    probs, classes = ps.topk(1)
    probs = probs.data.cpu().numpy().squeeze()
    classes = classes.data.cpu().numpy().squeeze()
    return probs, classes

def predict_csv(main_dir,csv_name):
    df = pd.read_csv(os.path.join(main_dir,'sample_submission.csv'))  
    count = 0
    for main_dir,sub_dir,file_name_list in os.walk(test_dir):
        for filename in file_name_list:    
            count += 1
            img_path = os.path.join(test_dir,filename)
            prob, classes = predict(img_path,model,device)    
            id = int(filename.split('.')[0])
            label = classes        
            df.loc[df[df['id']==id].index,['label']] = label
            # print('id:{},label:{}'.format(id,label))
            print('progress:{}/{}'.format(count,len(file_name_list)),end='\r')
    df.to_csv(os.path.join(main_dir,csv_name), index=None)

def resnet50_pred_to_csv(model,img_test_path, topn=5):
    list = []
    count = 0
    for filename in os.listdir(img_test_path):
        count += 1
        file_path = os.path.join(img_test_path, filename)
        img = image.load_img(file_path, target_size=(224, 224))
        x = image.img_to_array(img)
        x = np.expand_dims(x, axis=0)
        x = preprocess_input(x)
        preds = model.predict(x)
        topn_preds = decode_predictions(preds, top=topn)[0]
        topn_code = [x[0] for x in topn_preds]
        is_dog = len(set(topn_code) & set(dogs)) > 0 #
        id = int(filename.split('.')[0])
        label = 1 if is_dog else 0
        d = {'id':id,'label':label}
        list.append(d)
        print('count:{},id:{},label:{}'.format(count,id,label),end='\r')
        
    df = pd.DataFrame(list)
    df.to_csv('dogs-vs-cats-redux-kernels-edition\\resnet50_predict.csv',index=None)
